AGENT ParallelN
VERSION 1.0
TRUST_LEVEL 2
PURPOSE Compute dynamic parallel branch count N from Phase 1 risk_clusters
GOAL Select N active branches from the fixed-order BRANCH_POOL based on risk profile
     Guarantee rival branch always present by enforcing N >= 2
     Escalate branch depth proportionally to risk severity

RECEIVES risk_clusters: list
EMITS n_branches: int, active_branches: list
MUTATES nothing
CANNOT_MUTATE branch_pool_order, high_risk_set, n_table, rival_branch_required

CONSTRAINT BRANCH_POOL is a fixed tuple of exactly 8 entries in immutable order
CONSTRAINT HIGH_RISK_SET contains exactly medical legal financial safety
CONSTRAINT N is always the first N consecutive entries of BRANCH_POOL
CONSTRAINT N minimum is 2 — single-branch runs violate rival_branch_required
CONSTRAINT N maximum is 8 — equal to pool size
CONSTRAINT High-risk flag takes priority over count-based N rules
CONSTRAINT Rival is always the branch with the second-highest overall score
CONSTRAINT Active branches are always sliced from BRANCH_POOL[:N] in pool order

RULES
- Define BRANCH_POOL as immutable tuple in order:
    SafetyBranch FastBranch SkepticBranch CreativeBranch
    DetailBranch CautionBranch RivalBranch EvidenceBranch
- Define HIGH_RISK_SET as frozenset: medical legal financial safety
- On any HIGH_RISK_SET member present in risk_clusters: set N to 8
- On empty risk_clusters: set N to 2
- On exactly one non-high-risk cluster: set N to 4
- On two or more non-high-risk clusters: set N to 6
- Active branches are BRANCH_POOL[:N]
- Validate N does not exceed pool size before running — raise BranchPoolExhausted
- Validate risk_clusters is a list — raise BranchInputError on wrong type
- All N branches run in parallel via ThreadPoolExecutor
- Sort results by overall score descending
- Winner is results[0]; rival is results[1] — CANNOT_MUTATE

PROCESS
- Receive risk_clusters from Phase 1 LatentTrace
- Validate risk_clusters type is list
- Check for any HIGH_RISK_SET membership
- On high-risk match: N is 8
- On empty list: N is 2
- On one cluster non-high-risk: N is 4
- On two or more clusters non-high-risk: N is 6
- Validate N against pool size
- Slice BRANCH_POOL to get active_branches
- Launch N parallel branch workers
- Collect and sort results
- Return winner and rival

CHECK
- Empty risk_clusters produces N of 2 and active_branches SafetyBranch FastBranch
- Single non-high-risk cluster produces N of 4
- Two non-high-risk clusters produce N of 6
- Any high-risk cluster present produces N of 8 regardless of count
- All four high-risk labels individually produce N of 8
- BRANCH_POOL element assignment raises TypeError
- Non-list risk_clusters raises BranchInputError
- N above pool size raises BranchPoolExhausted
- Rival is always second-highest scoring branch
- Active branch order always matches BRANCH_POOL prefix order

WHEN
- risk_empty:    activate TwoBranchRun
- risk_single:   activate FourBranchRun
- risk_multiple: activate SixBranchRun
- risk_high:     activate EightBranchRun

FAILURE
- On non-list risk_clusters: raise BranchInputError with type name
- On N exceeding len(BRANCH_POOL): raise BranchPoolExhausted with N and pool size
- On branch execution error: return error string in response field, score normally

CONCEPT DynamicBranchDepth
PURPOSE Scale parallel reasoning depth to constitutional risk exposure
APPLIES WHEN risk_clusters available from Phase 1
NOT WHEN risk_clusters absent or not yet computed
PRIORITY 1
REQUIRES N computed before any branch is launched
REQUIRES BRANCH_POOL order is never altered at runtime
EFFECT higher-risk questions receive deeper branch coverage and more rival perspectives

CONCEPT RivalBranchGuarantee
PURPOSE Ensure every MultiplexResult carries a rival for constitutional comparison
APPLIES WHEN N >= 2 always
NOT WHEN N < 2 which is unconstitutional
PRIORITY 1
REQUIRES N minimum enforced at 2 by N-table design
EFFECT Sovereign can always compare winner against rival — no single-branch monopoly

OUTPUT
- n_branches: int one of 2 4 6 8
- active_branches: list of branch names, first N from BRANCH_POOL in pool order
- MultiplexResult: winner BranchResult, rival BranchResult, branches all N results

SUCCESS
pool_order_immutable:    0.30
n_selection_correct:     0.40
rival_always_present:    0.30
